=head2 v5.33  June ???, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

Replaced the self knitted SUPER in mv_all_methods with a real SUPER
call.

Added an Intro chapter to the manpage and deleted the details of the
upgrade from 4.23 to 5.00.

Changed the search for pod2man to look into scriptdirexp instead of
lib (Thanks, Ulrich Pfeifer!)

Made VMS::manifypod and Unix::manifypod more similar, preparing a
split into two smaller methods.

Moved cflags, const_loadlibs, and const_cccmd in front of
postconstants and pasthru. Very important bug fix!

Fixed the two my ... masks earlier declaration in same scope bugs in
Manifest. (Thanks, Gurusamy Sarathy!)

Added a pointer to ExtUtils::embed to the manpage.

Added .NO_CONFIG_REC for clearcase users.

=head2 v5.32  May 5, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

This release's main purpose is to eliminate left over hard coded
slashes, dots, dot-dots etc. to make porting easier for Matthias
Neeracher, the Mac porter. Thanks, for the helpful comments, Matthias.

Skip pods when scanning VERSION_FROM and do so in a separate
subroutine, so other programs may use this version parsing method
(MM->parse_version($file))

Set $| to 1 if verbose. (Ilya)

Improve catdir in MM_Unix: it now returns "/" on &catdir("/"). All "/"
operations are done via substr and length for maximum performance.

Introduce three new directory methods: curdir, rootdir, updir. All
three simply return strings: ".", "/", and "..". This is considered an
interim solution until we have a File::Generic module.

Canonpath removes successive slashes, successive "/.", trailing
slashes and leading "./".

Deprecated ROOTEXT (it was defined as "with leading slash" and broke
any portability. Introduced PARENT_NAME instead, which is Foo::Bar for
Foo::Bar::Baz.

Ilya's patch that enables manual setting of TEST_FILE and TESTDB_SW is
in. (Undocumented feature: make testdb TEST_FILE=foo TESTDB_SW=-d:DProf)

Ilya's patch to convert OS2 files to unix line ending conventions is
in.

Applied Charles' NOOP fix (NOOP was lost in a previous patch)

=head2 v5.31  April 21, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

Deleting single entries in %INC still caused troubles in 5.30, at
least when 5.002_01 built Tk-b11.02 we got a core dump. The only
remaining chance is to get rid of the code that deletes these keys and
teach our users not to use ad-hoc libraries in their Makefile.PLs
except these ad-hoc libraries can have a guaranteed namespace.

The DIR attribute accepted symlinks in all previous
MakeMakers. Dropped this to force portablility and disable the
potential for endless loopings.

Fixed the dependency MAP_TARGET -> static.

Install: There is a new macro called VERBINST which determines the
verbosity of the 'make install' target. Defaults to 1. 0 is pretty
silent, 2 is rather noisy. I leave it undocumented for now. Let me
know, how it goes for you. (Just like UNINST, VERBINST is only a macro
in the Makefile, not an attribute to the MakeMaker object, but I'm
open for the future)

Ilya's patches "Assorted patches to MakeMaker" of Tue, 16 Apr are in
except for the one change: $Config{bin_sh} is replaced with
$Config{sh}.

In manifypods I found a place where a "read on closed filehandle" was
possible. Fixed that.

Fixed the places with 'while ($something)' spotted by Sarathy.

Moved the $SIG{__WARN__} into inside WriteMakefile with a local()
declaration.

=head2 v5.29/30  April 11, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

Reenabled testing through subdirectories after MM-5.25's testdb patch
disabled it.

Made postamble the very last subroutine call again.

Introduced the macro UNINST which is 0 as a default and is not
settable from Makefile.PL, only on the 'make install' command
line. UNINST=1 will have the effect, that both shadowing and shadowed
files are unlinked. UNINST=0, the default, will write a warning at the
end of the install routine like so:

    ## Differing version of ExtUtils/Install.pm found. You might like to
    rm /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/site_perl/ExtUtils/Install.pm
    ## Differing versions of ExtUtils/MakeMaker.pm found. You might like to
    rm /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/site_perl/IP22-irix/ExtUtils/MakeMaker.pm
    rm /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/site_perl/ExtUtils/MakeMaker.pm
    ## Running 'make install UNINST=1' will unlink all those files for you.

Ulrich Pfeifer sent me a fix for manifypods (was not called unless we
had pods for section 3, now is also called if we have pods for section
1)

Changed the Makefile.PL so it doesn't autosplit Install anymore.

Fixed the code that deletes selected entries from %INC: It broke
MakeMaker for the perl distribution.

=head2 v5.28  April 9, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

Dropped support for the %att hash that was in use until MakeMaker-4.18.

Dropped %NORMAL_INC. Background: %NORMAL_INC was used to determine,
how we have to selectively delete elements of %INC in order to enable
repeated inclusion of History.pm or Configure.pm or other pm files
only used to configure one module. This had unpleasant side effects,
When libraries were in use, that use prototypes: File::Copy was
forgotten in %NORMAL_INC, and so was use()d several times. Instead of
adding File::Copy to %NORMAL_INC, I preferred to delete selectively
any pm file from %INC, that has a relative place in the filesystem.

Fixed the cflags bug (hash-elements/shell-elements mixed wrongly). Oh
buy, what a stupid bug did I introduce recently...

Reintroduced two blanks in the constants section.

Fixed the quoting in MANIFYPODS, so path names containing '@' will
work.


=head2 v5.27  April 4, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

The prompt function has changed a little: uses prototype, doesn't
display a default, if their isn't a default.

Rearranged the subroutines in MM_Unix to be in alphabetical order.

Ulrich Pfeifer pointed out, that scripts should be installed into
INSTALLSCRIPT not INSTALLBIN. So I introduced a new directory
blib/script and a new attribute INST_SCRIPT and deprecated
INST_EXE. Till March 97 INST_EXE will be turned into INST_SCRIPT for
backwards compatibility. A newly introduced INST_BIN directory
(blib/bin) will hold real binary files.

'make install' now uninstalls both shadowing and shadowed *.pm files
if they are different from the currently installed file. E.g.:
# echo junk > /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/site_perl/ExtUtils/Install.pm
# make install 
/usr/local/perl5.002_01/bin/perl -MAutoSplit -e 'autosplit("lib/ExtUtils/Install.pm","./blib/lib/auto");'
...
Skipping /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/ExtUtils/Install.pm (unchanged)
Unlinking /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/site_perl/ExtUtils/Install.pm (shadowing?)
Skipping /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/ExtUtils/Manifest.pm (unchanged)
...
Skipping /usr/local/perl5.002_01/man/man3/ExtUtils::MM_OS2.3 (unchanged)
Writing /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/IP22-irix/5.00201/auto/ExtUtils/MakeMaker/.packlist
Appending installation info to /usr/local/perl5.002_01/lib/IP22-irix/5.00201/perllocal.pod
#

Ilya's unlink_force patch is in Install.

Ilya's speedup for reading DATA handle is in.

Ilya's path_name_is_absolute patch is in.

Reverted back to $Config{osname} instead of $^O, because I want to
have a MakeMaker that needs only perl5.002.

Reverted back to simple "depend" relations without a NOOP (but leaving
all other NOOPs after :: dependencies) (Hint from Dean Roehrich)

Reverted back to DISTVNAME = \$(DISTNAME)-\$(VERSION) instead of
VERSION_SYM. (Hint from Ulrich Pfeifer)

$(INST_STATIC) e.g. DynaLoader.a now gets removed before we build
it. (Hint from Tim Bunce)

Permissions are now set to a+rX during make install. (Hint from Rodger
Anderson)

Introduced INST_SCRIPT and INSTALLSCRIPT to take over the role of
INST_EXE and INSTALLBIN, but leaving the latter intact. (Hint from
Ulrich Pfeifer)

Dean's patch to remove PMs during make realclean is in.

Dean's patch to check for has_link_code for realclean is in.

Dean's patch for INCLUDE_EXT and EXCLUDE_EXT is in.

Doesn't run all the xsubpp routines anymore if we don't need linking.

OPTIMIZE now is propagated to MAP_LINKCMD.

=head2 v5.26  March, 1996 by Charles Bailey

This is the version that came with perl5.002_01.

=head2 v5.25  February 29, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

Ilya's testdb patch is in. I left it undocumented as it needs more
thinking. Didn't come around to develop a more generic approach.

Now require()s 5.002.

Now runs autosplit on ExtUtils::Install in time.

Now suppresses the warning "blib/lib doesn't seem to be a perl library
directory".

Muchly improved documentation of methods overridable in the MY class.

Reduced the number of overridable methods via the MY class. The
reduction is very defensive. More reductions will follow in the future
after a careful analysis what's being overriden on CPAN packages.

Replaced the SelfLoader with my own autoloader. I couldn't do that
before because of NETaa15299 (pods in evals caused memory corruption).
This brings a further speedup: 

    MM_Unix with Selfloader:
    perl Makefile.PL  4.34s user 0.57s system 84% cpu 5.844 total
    make  14.77s user 3.16s system 78% cpu 22.698 total
    
    MM_Unix with my own autoloader
    perl Makefile.PL  3.82s user 0.55s system 73% cpu 5.920 total
    make  14.70s user 3.27s system 82% cpu 21.714 total

Both measures add up to a significant speedup with Tk-b9.01: 'perl
Makefile.PL' needs 
    18.10s user 5.79s system 63% cpu 37.614 total
compared to 5.23:
    28.51s user 5.37s system ???

=head2 v5.24  February 27, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

5.23 was not able to install itself if 5.21 was standard
MakeMaker. Fixed in this version.

What about an attribute that disables Version_check on your request? I
called it NO_VC. This shouldn't really go into your Makefile.PLs for
obvious reasons. Try 'perl Makefile.PL NO_VC=1' and enjoy this one
second for yourself :-)

=head2 v5.23  February 25, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

Ilya's zipdist support patch is in.

Chip's patch to remove targets before copying is in.

Ilya's patch to compute $Is_OS2 earlier is in.

Ilya's patch to catdir is in (trailing slash).

Dean's two C++ patches are in (more filename extensions)

Ilya's pure_all patch is in (no manify for test)

Assorted speedups: Free memory after a Makefile is flushed if we have
a parent. Skip all sections dist* and install in objects that have a
parent. Replaced the voluminous comment in extliblist with a pointer
to ExtUtils::Liblist. Xsubpp_Version is computed only once and stored
in a global. Reintroduced SelfLoader for MM_Unix and an own AUTOLOADER
for MakeMaker.

Version_check time:

          MM 5.21            MM 5.23
         real 5.63          real 1.79
         user 4.96          user 1.28
         sys  0.23          sys  0.13

Time for writing the Makefiles for Tk-b9 dropped from

	66.72s user 9.30s system

to

	28.51s user 5.37s system

on my Indy.

This is important: changed the move_all_methods subroutine so that
only methods that are already defined in MY will be moved to the
PACKnnnn class. This means, that any direct call to a MY->method
(instead of a $self->method call) might break the flow. I haven't
found such a Makefile. Tk-b8 had, I think such a call, but as Tk-b8
won't build on 5.002, this seems harmless to me.

Replaced the installpm method with an pm_to_blib method. This writes a
much more compact Makefile and delegates the whole PM hash to a perl
program (including autosplit) during make. This is much faster
especially for large extensions. The price is a new timestamp file
with the name "pm_to_blib".

Do not use FileHandle anymore, it's drag slow. See the top of MM_Unix
for some timings.

Deleted VERSION_FROM from CONFIG_DEP, instead inserted a warning in
'make dist' when VERSION_FROM is newer than Makefile.

Corrected documentation of shardist, tardist, zipdist (PREOP after
distdir)

Deleted the help() function (Note: 'make help' calls perldoc
ExtUtils::MakeMaker anyway).

ExtUtils::Manifest now uses File::Copy.

Introduced OPTIMIZE (and friends from cflags) as a variable for easy
setting of -g.

Added ExtUtils::testlib, Tim's clever pragma.

Replaced the Announce file with a README, so it will be seen on CPAN.

Replaced the old mechanism of attrib_help. We used to read the whole
pod documentation everytime WriteMakefile was called to determine,
which attributes are allowed in the WriteMakefile call. Now we
hardcode these attributes in the source, and 'make dist' runs a verify
script to check if documentation and the array of allowed attributes
are in sync.

Finally documented *all* MM_Unix methods with pods.

=head2 v5.21  February 6, 1996 by Andreas Koenig (came with 5.002gamma)

Introducing SelfLoader. Splitting into a bunch of new files: MM_Unix,
MM_VMS, MM_OS2, Install. Overall gain is excellent. Lots of dead
seconds could be saved. Unfortunately this not true. I couldn't
convince MakeMaker that it should run with SelfLoader, and I had to
comment the whole SelfLoader stuff for later investigation. We do have
considerable speedups still, but not the really big savings I saw with
SelfLoader. There is one very nasty interaction between SelfLoader and
Tk's Makefile.PLs, and only with Tk. See the commented stuff in
eval_in_subdirs in ExtUtils::MakeMaker to get an impression of the
whole story.

Permissions of the installed files were wrong.

Assorted patched by Ilya for OS/2 (IMPORT attribute).

OS2/ vs os/2 issues solved.

Enabled libscan to filter the directories that go into $self->{DIR} to
work around OS/2 behaviour, that calls the RCS file of Makefile.PL
just that: Makefile.PL.

Improved the automated rewriting of the Makefile by properly
seperating @ARGV for the second call into double quotes.

Made NOECHO complete functional for tricky rewritings of the
makefile. For example, I set NOECHO="date; time ", and got excellent
performance statistics without any extra work.

Deprecated exescan and writedoc.

Started to write the pods for ExtUtils::MM_Unix.

Introduced a new file: ExtUtils::Install. Handles install,
uninstall. .packlist files really work with this.

Liblist::ext is now a method. Safes us duplicate code.

Added basic pods to OS2 and VMS.

=head2 v5.19  February 4, 1996 by Andreas Koenig

Added documentation how the test target works.

Wrapped a comment out of EXPORT_OK that had slipped in there. Thanks,
Dean!

Added MakeMaker Revision number (RCS based) to generated Makefile for
easier debugging during development.

Install to sitelib: Introduce INSTALLSITELIB and INSTALLSITEARCH and
make the relationship between installsitelib and installsitearch the
same as the one between installprivlib and installarchlib. Introduce
INSTALLDIRS to enable selection between the two pairs. Introduce
SITELIBEXP and SITEARCHEXP to read from. Include SITEARCHEXP in the
directories to be searched for by makeaperl. Split the targets
install, reorg_packlist, and uninstall each into two, dedicating one
for "perl" and the other for "site".

Cleaned up method constants: rewritten to use simple foreach loops for
most of the constants.

Fixed a bug that didn't allow to set NOECHO to "". Makes debugging
easier for me.

Changed the layout of the blib directory again, sorry: the
subdirectories now: lib, arch, bin, man1, man3. This enables a
straightforward mapping of build and install directories.

This layout enables us to do the 'make install' step by simply copying
the files from the INST_* directories to the INSTALL* directories. The
copy is done by File::Copy. So this MakeMaker requires File::Copy be
included in the perl distribution.

The .packlist files are now written during the 'make install' and the
uninstall target is now a little bit more verbose.

Introduced AR_STATIC_ARGS defaulting to "cr" for making it easier on
the NeXT.

